CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 7, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand? On Hamilton Ave., Among the seven public liquor dispensing establishments on Hamilton Ave. are... (right photo, left to right): Al's Tavern, in the 6900 block, and Leonard's Tavern, in the 7000 block. Others are Wagner's and Fazio's at the Braddock - Hamilton intersection; The Rendezvous Cocktail Lounge in the 7200 block, and Bowser's at the intersection of Dallas and Hamilton Ave.... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Hamilton Avenue at Murtland Street with Al's Tavern and Leonard's Tavern, Homewood
